|Description = Part of the [[Sino-Tibetan languages|Sino-Tibetan]] language family, largely following Thurgood and La Polla (2003).<ref name=Thurgood>{{cite book|last1=Thurgood |first1=Graham |last2=LaPolla |first2=Randy J. (ed.s) |year=2003 |title=Sino-Tibetan Languages |location=[[London]] |publisher=[[Routledge]] |ISBN=0-7007-1129-5}}</ref> Here, the [[Monpa language|Monpa]] and [[Lepcha language|Lepcha]] languages are shown as sister languages to Old Tibetan (all are grouped into the [[Bodish languages|Bodic languages]]).
